examples.en: I'm not sure if I'm pronouncing this correctly.
If I remember correctly, he's Spanish.
Did I give you the correct change?
What's the correct answer to this question?
Wait a minute, let me see if I understand this correctly.
We must make sure that things are done correctly.
He corrects papers with a red pen.
Her watch never tells the correct time.
I hate it when she corrects my grammar.
If my memory serves me correctly, he lived in Paris for a while.
The company acted correctly in sacking him.
If you guess correctly, you have another turn.
Do you know how to punctuate a sentence correctly?
Our teacher hasn't finished correcting our tests yet.
He answered only three of the test questions correctly.
He was able to correctly identify the mushroom.
We are finding ways to correct this difficult situation.
Some pharmaceuticals can be quite risky unless taken correctly.
Reverse the i and e in recieve to spell receive correctly.
With the correct amount of water and sunlight, the plant will grow well.
If it is not treated correctly, the condition can prove fatal (=be fatal).
The system that pressurizes the airplane's cabin failed to operate correctly.
The treatment will continue until the patient reaches the point where he can walk correctly and safely.
Please correct your essay for punctuation errors.
Folding up this map correctly is such a nuisance.
